answers.answer: Id definitely tell your dr about it.
Stupid question maybe but does your bra fit correctly?
Yes I'd tell your Dr about thisMy Dr told me pains in that area could be signs of preeclamsia.

I thought it could be my bra too so I stopped wearing them for a couple days but it didn't help. My dr did say my blood pressure was a little on the high at my last visit. He asked me if I was having any other symptoms related to preeclamsia but I wasn't so he discarded it. :/ does preeclamsia effect delivery at all?
Um if you have a severe case of preeclampsia then they may try and take baby sooner as it can be dangerous for you and baby.

The good thing is your full term so if it is something to do with preeclampsia baby should be fine if they have to take him/her. But ask your doctor about this next time you go. High blood pressure ,chest pains and protein in the urine are symptoms along with some others.
